2.4 Age

  • Boxplots are used frequently in this section
  • Here is a reminder of what a boxplot displays:
    • The box represents the interquartile range (IQR) of the data
    • In other words, 50% of the patients fall between this age range
    • The thick black horizontal line is the median age
    • The thin black vertical lines extend to the upper and lower limits of age
    • Black dots represent outliers (above or below 3 x IQR)

2.4.4 Age of patients undergoing elective EVAR by decade of life

  • The number of elective EVARs by age of patient, grouped by decade of life:

  • Due to the small number of patients, those who were in their 6th or 10th decades at time of elective EVAR are ommitted from the following.
  • Boxplot of spread of ages in 7th, 8th or 9th decade:

  • Patients in their 7th decade skew slightly towards the upper aspect of that decade
  • Patients in their 8th decade, the decade in which most elective EVARs are performed, are evenly spread

  • Patients in their 9th decade skew greatly towards the young ages of that decade

  • The median and means from the above boxplot are shown in this table:

Decade Median Mean
7th 66.5 66.0
8th 75.0 74.6
9th 82.0 82.4

2.8 Seal zones and complexity

  • This section deals with seal zones for performed EVARs
  • Supra-renal seals comprises fEVAR and chEVAR
  • For the iliacs, CIA = common iliac artery, EIA = external iliac artery, AUI = aorto-uni-iliac device, IBD = iliac branch device
  • For AUI, the side where AUI is recorded is the occluded side (the contralateral side could be CIA, EIA etc.)
  • For IBD, seal in EIA is assumed
